events.1538: Santa Fe de Bogotá founded by Spanish conquistador Gonzalo Jiménez de Quesada.
events.1540: City status granted by Charles I of the Spanish Empire
events.1549: City becomes capital of the New Kingdom of Granada
events.1717: City becomes capital of the Viceroyalty of New Granada
events.1819: Battle of Boyacá and the Spanish evacuate. Santafé de Bogotá is renamed as Bogotá
events.1867: Universidad Nacional de Colombia (national university) is founded
events.1884: Compañía Colombiana de Teléfonos (telephone company) established
events.1886: Universidad Externado de Colombia and Escuela de Bellas Artes (school) founded
events.1910: Exposición del Centenario de la independencia (world's fair) held
events.1986: Pope John Paul II visits the city
events.2001: Colombian Securities Exchange headquartered in city
